## Always-on context (read, rarely rewrite)

| Rule | Role |
|------|------|
| `tenant-context.mdc` | When to open tenant catalogs |
| `project-architecture.mdc` | Boundaries, monorepo, templates vs layout |
| `../.cursor/rules/monorepo.mdc` | Repo root — frontend vs backend |

## Workflow

1. Identify which row(s) apply from the paths you will touch.
2. Read those `.mdc` files (and tenant catalog if applicable).
3. Make the code change.
4. Update every rule file whose documented behavior changed.

## Completion check

If your diff changes how the system works (routing, blocks, templates, data shape, integrations, CI) and **no** related `.mdc` was updated when the rule file documents that area, you are not done.
